<br>
This philosophy killed my guild.  People got to level 45 and thought they needed to join a big guild to do dragons and planes.  What irked me so much was *I* was already raiding dragons and planes with other guilds and told my guildmates I could get them invited as well.  <br>
<br>
Right now my guild consists of mainly inactive players.  Of the 3 others that play we have a 37 magician, 45 druid, and 52 warrior.  All very good friends and thats why we are still together.  So basically I'm &quot;indy&quot; or from one of those small guilds.  Not counting raids I've run I've been on 2 Nagafen raids, 1 Vox raid, 27 Hate raids, 22 Fear raids, 2 Growth raids, 1 Sky raid.   You do NOT need to be in a big guild or even a guild to do these things.  You just need to meet people and make friends. My guild never hosted raids on dragons and only 3 planes raids.  We partnered with Harpers, they are good friends and took any of my members that wanted to go. <br>
<br>
I am not better than anyone else on this server.  I just have been lucky enough to make friends and been able to do these things.  I didn't need to be in a guild to do any of these things. Neither does anyone else, all you have to do is meet people and make friends. <p><table>
