<br>
Please read my post - any guild stacking the rotation list with members is not tolerated today, so why would it be tolerated if Indies are banned or allowed to continue in the rotation?  Please - that is an abuse of the system we have in place.<br>
<br>
Twiggie:<br>
The vote before us is to allow or disallow individual raid leaders (Independant, unguilded, or &quot;Indie&quot;) from the rotation - this is an important issue that you can comment on.  Although your point about little guilds is important, you may wawnt to bring it up somewhere else, or maybe start another vote. I'd love to know your thoughts on indies.<br>
<br>
Tjon: <br>
I don't know you - never grouped with you, and I'm sure you're a fine player, but I'll tell you this - I'd rather go on Slayback's raid with you in it than yours with Slayback in it because I know Slayback and he knows how to manage a raid.  No offense to you, but I don't see how you being guilded (or not) has any bearing on weather or not you can run a good raid, and we're talking about LEADING a raid rather than fighting in it.<br>
<br>
Jaradis:<br>
